The evidence with the title 'Child mortality - our World In Data ' says Child mortality in rich countries today is much lower than 1%.  ... In the last century is “ the global child mortality rate fell by 0.0008 percentage points since yesterday ” . Big countries like Brazil and China reduced their child mortality rates 10 - fold ... Last 50 years ( 1 in 4 children died in the early 60s – today it is less than 1 in 10 ) .
